createPlayer(string).details: One address can only create one player.             Name cannot be empty string.

finishAttack(address,uint256).details: Player should finish their won battles to increase its points.             Attack must exists for a given attacker and starting minute.             Bitcoin prices for both the starting and ending minutes must be set.             Updates the corresponding attack and player structs.

params._startingMinute: Starting minute timestamp of the battle

getPlayers(uint256,uint256).details: Start ID of 0 means there is no lower limit while end ID of 0 means there is no upper limit.             This is sort of like a pagination since the players array can become quite big.             Start ID cannot be greater than the end ID.

returns._0: Players belongs to the given ID interval

getPrice(uint256).details: Returns only if the price is set.

params._minuteTimestamp: Minute timestamp of the requested price

params._startingMinute: Starting minute timestamp of the battle

returns._0: True if and only if attack has been registered

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

registerAttack(address,uint256,bool).details: Sender address is an attacker of battle and it must have a player.             Defender must have a player.             Player cannot attack itself.             Player can only register one attack for a given starting minute.             Starting minute of battle must be greater than current minute.             Starting minute of battle must not be too much greater than current minute (currently 1 hour).             This function adds a pending price request for a starting minute and the next (ending) minute.

params._side: Attacker price prediction which is true if and only if attacker predicted an increase
params._startingMinute: Starting minute timestamp of the battle

setPriceRequest(uint256,uint256).details: Only oracle can set the price request.             Removes the corresponding request from pending requests.             If price request of previous minute timestamp exists, then calculates the increase percent.

params._minuteTimestamp: Minute timestamp of the price request
